<title>USA: RESEARCH ALERT - PepsiCo raised.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT - PepsiCo raised.</headline>
<text>
<p>-- Schroder Wertheim said analyst Caroline Levy raised the rating on PepsiCo Inc to outperform from perform-in-line.</p>
<p>-- raised earnings estimate to $1.45 per share from $1.42 for 1997 and to $1.67 from $1.65 for 1998.</p>
<p>-- said that after private visit with company management this week, believes estimate for international beverages business was too low, and world snacks business &quot;could deliver an upside surprise based on margin expansion.&quot;</p>
<p>-- said that company has repurchased &quot;more shares than we anticipated in the fourth quarter, and should continue to be aggressive in 1997.&quot;</p>
<p>-- shares closed Tuesday at 29-1/4.</p>
</text>
